Question: Generate a code snippet in C++ that reverses a given string. Answer: Here's one way to reverse a string in C++ using the standard library:

```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
  std::string str = "hello world";
  std::cout << "Original string: " << str << '\n';

  // Reverse the string
  std::reverse(str.begin(), str.end());
  std::cout << "Reversed string: " << str << '\n';

  return 0;
}
```

This program will output:

```
Original string: hello world
Reversed string: dlrow olleh
```

The `std::reverse()` function is part of the `<algorithm>` header in the C++ standard library. It takes two iterators representing the start and end of a range, and reverses the elements in that range in place. In this case, we're passing in `str.begin()` and `str.end()` to reverse the entire string.

