Question: Create an efficient algorithm to count the number of elements in an array
Array: [3, 4, 7, 5, 1] Answer: 1. Initialize a variable count to 0
2. Iterate through each element in the array
3. For each element, add 1 to the count variable
4. After iterating through all the elements, the value of count will be equal to the number of elements in the array
5. Return the value of count as the result.

Time Complexity: O(n), where n is the number of elements in the array.
Space Complexity: O(1), as we only need one variable to keep track of the count. 

JavaScript code:

function countElements(arr) {
  let count = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    count++;
  }
  return count;
}

// Example usage:
const arr = [3, 4, 7, 5, 1];
